It was pretty clear they had been fried once, and dropped back in the fryer multiple times to warm up prior to getting to me.  First time eating here, so just tried the basics egg roll, soup, fried rice prior to getting into other dishes and likely will stick to the basics here.  If egg rolls are botched, my faith in other foods isn't that great, but solid for the basics.  If the egg roll was even edible without cringing, I would've given 4 stars.

If you like this restaurant, you don't know Chinese food from shoe leather.  I'm serious.  I ordered twice cooked pork and it was by far the worst twice cooked pork I have ever had.  Actually the only thing in it that is in traditional twice cooked pork was the pork.  But even that was stretching it, as they used a completely wrong cut of pork.  Every other ingredient in the dish is not an ingredient that is supposed to be in twice cooked pork.  Needless to say, it was missing all the crucial ingredients.  It tasted nothing like twice cooked pork.  And when I say nothing, I mean nothing as in the way steak tastes nothing like cream of broccoli soup.  Even if I give them the benefit of the doubt and assume they were making a different dish, I honestly don't know what that dish would be.  A moo goo gai pan ripoff with pork instead of chicken?  And preserved bamboo instead of fresh vegetables?  Possibly.  Except that dish doesn't exist in Chinese cooking.  Whatever it was they thought they were making, I can vividly describe what it tasted like:  decayed meat covered by a weak white wine based (as in mostly starch instead of wine) sauce.
